verbose_text: However, the numbers of p53 and Mdm2 molecules are typically very large : Measured levels of p53 range from 17,000 -200,000 molecules in different cell lines [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], and the resting level of p53 in our model, = ~ 100 nM, corresponds to 50,000 molecules per cell (assuming the cell is a sphere of radius around 6 mum).
